OL,3,CCancer patient thanks clinical trial
OL,4,Cfor years lived since terminal
OL,5,Cdiagnosis
OL,7,FThe 61-year-old was in hospital for
OL,8,Ftests after a bout of food poisoning
OL,9,Fwhen scans revealed something far
OL,10,Fworse.
OL,12,FTerry told ITV News that doctors found
OL,13,Fa "shadow" on his liver and then broke
OL,14,Fthe news by saying: "'I'm sorry -
OL,15,Fyou've got terminal cancer.'
OL,17,F"My reaction was: 'How long have I
OL,18,Fgot? Six days, six weeks, six months?'
OL,20,F"They told me I had six to twelve
OL,21,Fmonths."
