OL,3,CCancer patient thanks clinical trial
OL,4,Cfor years lived since terminal
OL,5,Cdiagnosis
OL,7,FTerry and his family are not just
OL,8,Fgrateful for the treatment advances
OL,9,Fthat have helped him, but grateful for
OL,10,Fthe dodgy meal which triggered medical
OL,11,Ftests in the first place.
OL,13,FWithout suffering from food poisoning,
OL,14,Fthe cancer would not have been found
OL,15,Fand he would not have been treated.
OL,17,FHe laughed as he said: "Of all things,
OL,18,Fa fish pie. So, really, it's a bit of
OL,19,Fluck saying 'thank you' to a fish pie!"
